               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Ṣavāʿiq-i muḥriqah by Ibn Ḥajar al-Hays̲amī</summary>
                  <msItem class="https://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010113603 https://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_263B-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Chapter or bāb nine from the 
                <title key="work_600">Ṣavāʿiq-i muḥriqah</title>, a larger collection of traditions and anecdotes by or relating to the 
                <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164657175.0x000001 viaf_34436377" role="subject">Khalīfah and Imām ʿAlī</persName>, written by the Shāfiʿī theologian, 
                <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100167332138.0x000001 viaf_100387532" role="aut">Shihāb al-Dīn Aḥmad ibn Muḥammad Ibn Ḥajar al-Hays̲amī</persName>(d. 974/1566), whose name does not appear in this copy that is probably part of a larger set of volumes now dispersed.
                        </p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 135v): completed at the dār al-mulk 
                <placeName>Bāns Barīlī</placeName>(
                <placeName>Bans Bareilly</placeName>, Uttar Pradesh), Jumādá al-Avval 1244/November-December 1828.
                        </p>
                        <p>Nastaʿlīq.</p>
                        <p>Annotations and corrections in margins.</p>
                        <p>Stamped foliation.</p>
                        <p>Lacking original covers.</p>
                        <p>Deep brown blind-tooled leather binging, gilded only along the spine.</p>
                        <p>Folios cropped; wormholes.</p>
                        <p>IOL Microfilm 478.</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_600">Ṣavāʿiq-i muḥriqah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_600">صواعق محرقه</title>
